{
  "texts": [
    "System-specific model For each system, a reference dataset is generated by running a short MD simulation (less than a nanosecond) using the reference model.",
    "For proteins and, more generally, for large systems, a fragmentation strategy similar to the one proposed in ref.",
    "37 was employed to reduce the computational burden while retaining local structural information.",
    "We then evaluate the energies and forces of the collected frames with the reference model.",
    "The on-the-fly system-specific model is then trained on this dataset, resulting in a model about 10 times faster than FeNNix-Bio1(M) with our current setup."
  ]
}